                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="72781" author="mark.pollack" created="Thu, 17 Nov 2011 09:23:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is around enforcing the conventions of mapping and populating Ids.  Will be fixed in issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-322&quot; title=&quot;Throw exception in a save operation if the POJO&amp;#39;s ID field is null and field type is not String, BigInteger or ObjectId.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATAMONGO-322&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATAMONGO-322&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73194" author="olivergierke" created="Tue, 29 Nov 2011 01:44:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So what is the exact issue we&apos;re talking about here? In the forums example you use a primitive &lt;tt&gt;int&lt;/tt&gt; which will simply default to a value if not set, which is in turn the value we write. So we simply cannot detect that the id shall be auto-populated if it already has a value. Can&apos;t you simply use an &lt;tt&gt;Integer&lt;/tt&gt; and leave that set to &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;. This should trigger auto-assignment of the id then.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the integer id being stored as a &lt;tt&gt;String&lt;/tt&gt; would you mind providing a test case showing that behaviour? As &lt;tt&gt;Integer&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;int&lt;/tt&gt; are types MongoDB can handle natively we do not convert them unless you provide a custom converter to do so.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73196" author="drypot" created="Tue, 29 Nov 2011 03:47:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wrote some related code in other forum thread.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springsource.org/showthread.php?117707-findById-returns-null&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springsource.org/showthread.php?117707-findById-returns-null&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;int type field is saved as int IF IT IS NOT @ID field.&lt;br/&gt;
int type @ID field is saved as String.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;findById(int) does not work either, returns null.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="73333" author="drypot" created="Thu, 1 Dec 2011 19:50:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
